1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with planar drawings of directed graphs, which is a topic closely related to computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the complexity of testing for the existence of planar L-drawings, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper provides necessary conditions for the existence of planar L-drawings, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses st-graphs, which are a type of directed graph used in game theory. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - Although not a major focus of the paper, the linear-time algorithm for computing a bitonic st-ordering could be relevant to distributed or parallel computing.
